01:33:49.470 --> 01:33:52.070
But is it true, Salerio?

1787
01:33:52.070 --> 01:33:53.530
Have all his venturesfailed?

1788
01:33:53.530 --> 01:33:54.730
What, not one hit?

1789
01:33:54.730 --> 01:33:57.230
From Tripolis, from Mexicoand England?

1790
01:33:57.230 --> 01:34:01.700
From Lisbon, Barbary, andIndia?

1791
01:34:01.700 --> 01:34:05.870
And not one vessel 'scapethe dreadful touch

1792
01:34:05.870 --> 01:34:07.170
of merchant-marring rocks?

1793
01:34:07.170 --> 01:34:08.570
Not one, my lord.

1794
01:34:08.570 --> 01:34:09.970
Besides, it should appearthat,

1795
01:34:09.970 --> 01:34:12.370
if he had the present moneyto discharge the Jew,

1796
01:34:12.370 --> 01:34:13.630
he would not take it.

1797
01:34:13.630 --> 01:34:16.370
Never did I know acreature that did bear theshape of man

1798
01:34:16.370 --> 01:34:19.430
so keen and greedy toconfound a man.

1799
01:34:19.430 --> 01:34:21.300
He plies the Duke atmorning and at night

1800
01:34:21.300 --> 01:34:23.100
and doth impeach thefreedom of the state

1801
01:34:23.100 --> 01:34:25.230
if they deny him justice.

1802
01:34:25.230 --> 01:34:28.100
Twenty merchants, the Dukehimself,

1803
01:34:28.100 --> 01:34:31.270
and the magnificoes ofgreatest port have allpersuaded with him.

1804
01:34:31.270 --> 01:34:34.130
But none can drive himfrom the envious plea

1805
01:34:34.130 --> 01:34:38.230
of forfeiture, of justice,and his bond.

1806
01:34:38.230 --> 01:34:40.870
When I was with him, Ihave heard him swear

1807
01:34:40.870 --> 01:34:43.300
to Tubal and to Chus, hiscountrymen,

1808
01:34:43.300 --> 01:34:45.530
that he would rather haveAntonio's flesh

1809
01:34:45.530 --> 01:34:47.500
than twenty times thevalue of the sum

1810
01:34:47.500 --> 01:34:48.770
that he did owe him.

1811
01:34:48.770 --> 01:34:51.030
And I know, my lord,

1812
01:34:51.030 --> 01:34:54.200
if law, authority, andpower deny not,

1813
01:34:54.200 --> 01:34:57.200
it will go hard with poorAntonio.

1814
01:34:57.200 --> 01:34:59.570
Is it your dear friendthat is thus in trouble?

1815
01:34:59.570 --> 01:35:02.670
The dearest friend to me,the kindest man,

1816
01:35:02.670 --> 01:35:06.600
the best-conditioned andunwearied spirit in doingcourtesies,

1817
01:35:06.600 --> 01:35:09.170
and one in whom theancient Roman honor moreappears

1818
01:35:09.170 --> 01:35:10.770
than any that draws breathin Italy.

1819
01:35:10.770 --> 01:35:12.330
What sum owes he the Jew?

1820
01:35:12.330 --> 01:35:15.000
For me, 3,000 ducats.

1821
01:35:15.000 --> 01:35:17.330
What, no more?

1822
01:35:17.330 --> 01:35:21.070
Pay him 6,000 and defacethe bond.

1823
01:35:21.070 --> 01:35:25.770
Double 6,000 and thentreble that before afriend of this description

1824
01:35:25.770 --> 01:35:27.730
shall lose a hair throughBassanio's fault.

1825
01:35:27.730 --> 01:35:33.230
First, go with me tochurch and call me wife

1826
01:35:33.230 --> 01:35:35.770
and then away to Venice toyour friend,

1827
01:35:35.770 --> 01:35:39.970
for never shall you lie byPortia's side with anunquiet soul.

1828
01:35:39.970 --> 01:35:43.730
You shall have gold to paythe petty debt twentytimes over.

1829
01:35:43.730 --> 01:35:46.100
When it is paid, bringyour true friend along.

1830
01:35:46.100 --> 01:35:50.200
My maid Nerissa and myselfmeantime will live asmaids and widows.

1831
01:35:50.200 --> 01:35:51.770
Come, away.

1832
01:35:51.770 --> 01:35:54.130
For you must hence uponyour wedding day.

1833
01:35:54.130 --> 01:35:55.430
Bid your friends welcome.

1834
01:35:55.430 --> 01:35:56.630
Show a merry cheer.

1835
01:35:56.630 --> 01:36:00.870
Since you are dear bought,I will love you dear.

1836
01:36:03.070 --> 01:36:05.830
But let me hear the letterof your friend.

1837
01:36:09.570 --> 01:36:13.070
"Sweet Bassanio, my shipshave all miscarried,

1838
01:36:13.070 --> 01:36:16.530
"my creditors grow cruel,my estate is very low,

1839
01:36:16.530 --> 01:36:18.600
"my bond to the Jew isforfeit,

1840
01:36:18.600 --> 01:36:22.570
"and since in paying it itis impossible I should live,

1841
01:36:22.570 --> 01:36:24.230
"all debts are clearedbetween you and I

1842
01:36:24.230 --> 01:36:27.400
"if I might but see you atmy death.

1843
01:36:27.400 --> 01:36:29.930
"Notwithstanding, use yourpleasure.

1844
01:36:29.930 --> 01:36:34.570
If your love do notpersuade you to come, letnot my letter."

1845
01:36:34.570 --> 01:36:38.400
Oh, love, dispatch allbusiness and be gone.

1846
01:36:38.400 --> 01:36:41.630
Since I have your goodleave to go away, I willmake haste.

1847
01:36:41.630 --> 01:36:43.270
But till I come again,

1848
01:36:43.270 --> 01:36:45.370
no bed shall e'er beguilty of my stay,

1849
01:36:45.370 --> 01:36:48.170
nor rest be interposer'twixt us twain.

1850
01:36:53.470 --> 01:36:54.970
Jailer, look to him.

1851
01:36:54.970 --> 01:36:57.200
Tell not me of mercy.

1852
01:36:57.200 --> 01:36:59.400
This is the fool that lentout money gratis.

1853
01:36:59.400 --> 01:37:00.600
Jailer, look to him.

1854
01:37:00.600 --> 01:37:01.730
Hear me yet, good Shylock.

1855
01:37:01.730 --> 01:37:03.030
I'll have my bond!

1856
01:37:03.030 --> 01:37:04.170
Speak not against my bond.

1857
01:37:04.170 --> 01:37:07.370
I have sworn an oath thatI will have my bond.

1858
01:37:07.370 --> 01:37:10.130
Thou call'dst me dogbefore thou hadst a cause,

1859
01:37:10.130 --> 01:37:12.900
but since I am a dog,beware my fangs.

1860
01:37:12.900 --> 01:37:16.000
The Duke shall grant mejustice.

1861
01:37:16.000 --> 01:37:18.970
I do wonder, thou naughtyjailer, that thou art so fond

1862
01:37:18.970 --> 01:37:20.900
to come abroad with him athis request.

1863
01:37:20.900 --> 01:37:22.170
I pray thee, hear mespeak.

1864
01:37:22.170 --> 01:37:23.430
I'll have my bond.

1865
01:37:23.430 --> 01:37:24.930
I will not hear theespeak.

1866
01:37:24.930 --> 01:37:28.100
I'll have my bond, andtherefore speak no more.

1867
01:37:28.100 --> 01:37:31.900
I'll not be made a softand dull-eyed fool

1868
01:37:31.900 --> 01:37:35.000
to shake the head, relent,and sigh,

1869
01:37:35.000 --> 01:37:36.570
and yield to Christianintercessors.

1870
01:37:36.570 --> 01:37:37.900
Follow not.

1871
01:37:37.900 --> 01:37:39.530
I'll have no speaking.

1872
01:37:39.530 --> 01:37:42.130
I will have my bond.

1873
01:37:42.130 --> 01:37:45.200
It is the mostimpenetrable cur that everkept with man.

1874
01:37:45.200 --> 01:37:47.000
Let him alone.

1875
01:37:47.000 --> 01:37:49.100
I'll follow him no morewith bootless prayers.

1876
01:37:49.100 --> 01:37:50.400
He seeks my life.

1877
01:37:50.400 --> 01:37:52.730
His reason well I know.

1878
01:37:52.730 --> 01:37:54.700
I oft delivered from hisforfeitures

1879
01:37:54.700 --> 01:37:57.500
many that have at timesmade moan to me.

1880
01:37:57.500 --> 01:37:59.300
Therefore he hates me.

1881
01:37:59.300 --> 01:38:03.470
I am sure the Duke willnever grant thisforfeiture to hold.

1882
01:38:03.470 --> 01:38:05.200
The Duke cannot deny thecourse of law.

1883
01:38:05.200 --> 01:38:07.900
For the commodity thatstrangers have with us inVenice,

1884
01:38:07.900 --> 01:38:09.470
if it be denied, will muchimpeach

1885
01:38:09.470 --> 01:38:12.130
the justice of the state sincethat the trade and profit

1886
01:38:12.130 --> 01:38:15.930
of the city consisteth ofall nations.

1887
01:38:15.930 --> 01:38:19.700
Therefore, go.

1888
01:38:19.700 --> 01:38:23.300
These griefs and losseshave so bated me

1889
01:38:23.300 --> 01:38:28.200
that I shall hardly sparea pound of flesh tomorrowto my bloody creditor.

1890
01:38:28.200 --> 01:38:32.570
Well, jailer, on.

1891
01:38:36.600 --> 01:38:40.800
Pray God Bassanio come tosee me pay his debt.

1892
01:38:44.030 --> 01:38:45.800
And then I care not.

1893
01:38:50.400 --> 01:38:53.500
Madam, although I speak itin your presence,

1894
01:38:53.500 --> 01:38:55.630
you have a noble and atrue conceit

1895
01:38:55.630 --> 01:38:58.900
of godlike amity, whichappears most strongly

1896
01:38:58.900 --> 01:39:01.530
in bearing thus theabsence of your lord.

1897
01:39:01.530 --> 01:39:04.070
But if you knew to whomyou show this honor,

1898
01:39:04.070 --> 01:39:06.470
how true a gentleman yousend relief,

1899
01:39:06.470 --> 01:39:08.570
how dear a lover of mylord, your husband,

1900
01:39:08.570 --> 01:39:11.300
I know you would beprouder of the work

1901
01:39:11.300 --> 01:39:13.130
than customary bounty canenforce you.

1902
01:39:13.130 --> 01:39:16.370
I never did repent for doinggood, nor shall not now.

1903
01:39:16.370 --> 01:39:20.930
For in companions that doconverse and waste thetime together

1904
01:39:20.930 --> 01:39:23.570
whose souls do bear anequal yoke of love,

1905
01:39:23.570 --> 01:39:25.600
there must be needs a likeproportion

1906
01:39:25.600 --> 01:39:27.770
of lineaments, of manners,and of spirit,

1907
01:39:27.770 --> 01:39:31.500
which makes me think thatthis Antonio, being thebosom lover of my lord,

1908
01:39:31.500 --> 01:39:33.070
must needs be like mylord.

1909
01:39:33.070 --> 01:39:36.970
If it be so, how little isthe cost I have bestowed

1910
01:39:36.970 --> 01:39:38.900
in purchasing thesemblance of my soul

1911
01:39:38.900 --> 01:39:41.600
from out the state ofhellish cruelty.

1912
01:39:41.600 --> 01:39:44.200
But this comes too nearthe praising of myself.

1913
01:39:44.200 --> 01:39:45.500
Therefore, no more of it.

1914
01:39:45.500 --> 01:39:47.130
Hear other things.

1915
01:39:47.130 --> 01:39:49.670
Lorenzo, I commit intoyour hands

1916
01:39:49.670 --> 01:39:53.770
the husbandry and manageof my house until mylord's return.

1917
01:39:53.770 --> 01:39:57.800
For mine own part, I havetoward heaven breathed asecret vow

1918
01:39:57.800 --> 01:40:02.200
to live in prayer andcontemplation onlyattended by Nerissa here

1919
01:40:02.200 --> 01:40:05.230
until her husband and mylord's return.

1920
01:40:05.230 --> 01:40:08.330
There is a monastery threemiles off, and there wewill abide.

1921
01:40:08.330 --> 01:40:10.870
I do desire you not todeny this imposition,

1922
01:40:10.870 --> 01:40:15.000
the which my love and somenecessity now lays uponyou.

1923
01:40:15.000 --> 01:40:17.970
Madam, with all my heart Ishall obey you in all faircommands.

1924
01:40:17.970 --> 01:40:19.530
My people do already knowmy mind

1925
01:40:19.530 --> 01:40:24.170
and will acknowledge youand Jessica in place oflord Bassanio and myself.

1926
01:40:24.170 --> 01:40:26.570
So fare you well till weshall meet again.

1927
01:40:26.570 --> 01:40:30.000
Fair thoughts and happyhours attend on you.

1928
01:40:30.000 --> 01:40:31.800
I wish your ladyship allheart's content.

1929
01:40:31.800 --> 01:40:33.100
I thank you for your wish,

1930
01:40:33.100 --> 01:40:36.400
and I'm well pleased towish it back on you.

1931
01:40:38.600 --> 01:40:40.130
Fare ye well, Jessica.

1932
01:40:42.530 --> 01:40:47.330
Now, Balthasar, as I haveever found thee honest-true,

1933
01:40:47.330 --> 01:40:48.930
so let me find thee still.

1934
01:40:48.930 --> 01:40:50.330
Take this same letter,

1935
01:40:50.330 --> 01:40:53.430
and use thou all theendeavor of a man in speedto Padua.

1936
01:40:53.430 --> 01:40:56.430
See thou deliver this intomy cousin's hand, Dr.Bellario.

1937
01:40:56.430 --> 01:40:58.630
And look what notes andgarments he doth give thee.

1938
01:40:58.630 --> 01:41:01.230
Bring them, I pray thee,with imagined speed untothe traject,

1939
01:41:01.230 --> 01:41:02.970
to the common ferry whichtrades to Venice.

1940
01:41:02.970 --> 01:41:04.200
Waste no time in words.

1941
01:41:04.200 --> 01:41:05.470
Get thee gone.

1942
01:41:05.470 --> 01:41:07.070
I shall be there beforethee.

1943
01:41:07.070 --> 01:41:10.400
Madam, I go with allconvenient speed.

1944
01:41:10.400 --> 01:41:11.830
Come on, Nerissa.

1945
01:41:11.830 --> 01:41:15.070
I have work in hand thatyou yet know not of.

1946
01:41:15.070 --> 01:41:17.700
We'll see our husbandsbefore they think of us.

1947
01:41:17.700 --> 01:41:18.870
Shall they see us?

1948
01:41:18.870 --> 01:41:20.970
They shall, Nerissa, butin such a habit

1949
01:41:20.970 --> 01:41:24.430
that they shall think weare accomplished with thatwe lack.

1950
01:41:24.430 --> 01:41:25.730
I'll hold thee any wager

1951
01:41:25.730 --> 01:41:28.430
when we are bothaccoutered like young men,

1952
01:41:28.430 --> 01:41:30.430
I'll prove the prettierfellow of the two

1953
01:41:30.430 --> 01:41:32.500
and wear my dagger withthe braver grace

1954
01:41:32.500 --> 01:41:36.230
and speak between thechange of man and boy in areed voice

1955
01:41:36.230 --> 01:41:39.770
and turn two mincing stepsinto a manly stride

1956
01:41:39.770 --> 01:41:42.900
and speak of frays like afine bragging youth

1957
01:41:42.900 --> 01:41:46.370
and tell quaint lies howhonorable ladies sought mylove,

1958
01:41:46.370 --> 01:41:48.370
which I denying, they fellsick and died.

1959
01:41:48.370 --> 01:41:49.670
I could not do withal.

1960
01:41:49.670 --> 01:41:51.730
And then I'll repent andwish, for all that,

1961
01:41:51.730 --> 01:41:53.030
that I had not killedthem.

1962
01:41:53.030 --> 01:41:55.970
And twenty of these punylies I'll tell that menshall swear

1963
01:41:55.970 --> 01:41:58.230
I have discontinued schoolabove a twelvemonth.

1964
01:41:58.230 --> 01:41:59.970
I have, within my mind,

1965
01:41:59.970 --> 01:42:02.470
a thousand raw tricks ofthese bragging jacks

1966
01:42:02.470 --> 01:42:04.000
which I will practice.

1967
01:42:04.000 --> 01:42:05.430
Why, shall we turn to men?

1968
01:42:05.430 --> 01:42:09.030
Fie, what a question'sthat if thou wert near alewd interpreter.

1969
01:42:09.030 --> 01:42:11.870
But come, I'll tell theeall my whole device

1970
01:42:11.870 --> 01:42:14.770
when I'm in my coach,which stays for us at thepark gate.

1971
01:42:14.770 --> 01:42:19.130
Therefore haste away, forwe must measure twentymiles today.

1972
01:42:20.630 --> 01:42:23.370
Yes, truly, for look you,the sins of the father

1973
01:42:23.370 --> 01:42:25.200
are to be laid upon thechildren.

1974
01:42:25.200 --> 01:42:27.930
Therefore, I promise you,I fear you.

1975
01:42:27.930 --> 01:42:29.930
I was always plain withyou.

1976
01:42:29.930 --> 01:42:32.630
And so now I speak myagitation of the matter.

1977
01:42:32.630 --> 01:42:37.500
Therefore be of goodcheer, for truly I thinkyou are damned.

1978
01:42:37.500 --> 01:42:40.870
There is but one hope in itthat can do you any good

1979
01:42:40.870 --> 01:42:43.500
and that is but a kind ofbastard hope neither.

1980
01:42:43.500 --> 01:42:45.830
And what hope is that, Ipray thee?

1981
01:42:45.830 --> 01:42:49.670
Marry, you may partly hopethat your father got you not,

1982
01:42:49.670 --> 01:42:52.130
that you are not the Jew'sdaughter.

1983
01:42:52.130 --> 01:42:54.930
That were a kind ofbastard hope indeed.

1984
01:42:54.930 --> 01:42:58.430
So the sins of my mothershould be visited upon me.

1985
01:42:58.430 --> 01:43:01.970
Truly then, I fear you aredamned

1986
01:43:01.970 --> 01:43:03.700
both by father and mother.

1987
01:43:03.700 --> 01:43:06.530
Thus when I shun Scylla,your father,

1988
01:43:06.530 --> 01:43:08.770
I fall into Charybdis,your mother.

1989
01:43:08.770 --> 01:43:11.530
Well, you are gone bothways.

1990
01:43:11.530 --> 01:43:13.400
I shall be saved by myhusband.

1991
01:43:13.400 --> 01:43:15.000
He hath made me aChristian.

1992
01:43:15.000 --> 01:43:16.400
Truly, the more to blamehe.

1993
01:43:16.400 --> 01:43:18.230
We were Christians enoughbefore

1994
01:43:18.230 --> 01:43:20.470
e'en as many could welllive one by another.

1995
01:43:20.470 --> 01:43:24.030
This making of Christianswill raise the price of hogs.

1996
01:43:24.030 --> 01:43:26.570
If we grow all to bepork-eaters,

1997
01:43:26.570 --> 01:43:29.270
we shall not shortly have arasher on the coals for money.

1998
01:43:29.270 --> 01:43:32.200
I'll tell my husband,Launcelot, what you say.

1999
01:43:32.200 --> 01:43:34.070
Here he comes.

2000
01:43:40.770 --> 01:43:43.070
I shall grow jealous ofyou shortly, Launcelot,

2001
01:43:43.070 --> 01:43:47.070
if you thus get my wifeinto corners.

2002
01:43:47.070 --> 01:43:49.200
Nay, you need not fear us,Lorenzo.

2003
01:43:49.200 --> 01:43:51.170
Launcelot and I are out.

2004
01:43:51.170 --> 01:43:54.900
He tells me flatly there'sno mercy for me in heaven

2005
01:43:54.900 --> 01:43:56.570
because I am a Jew'sdaughter.

2006
01:43:56.570 --> 01:44:00.130
And he says you are nogood member of thecommonwealth,

2007
01:44:00.130 --> 01:44:05.330
for in converting Jews toChristians, you raise theprice of pork.

2008
01:44:05.330 --> 01:44:07.370
I shall answer that betterto the commonwealth

2009
01:44:07.370 --> 01:44:10.170
than you can the gettingup of the negro's belly.

2010
01:44:10.170 --> 01:44:14.130
The moor is with child byyou, Launcelot.

2011
01:44:14.130 --> 01:44:19.500
Well, it is much that the moorshould be more than reason.

2012
01:44:19.500 --> 01:44:22.000
But if she be less than anhonest woman,

2013
01:44:22.000 --> 01:44:24.430
she is indeed more than Itook her for.

2014
01:44:24.430 --> 01:44:27.130
How every fool can playupon the word.

2015
01:44:27.130 --> 01:44:30.570
I think the best grace ofwit will shortly turn intosilence

2016
01:44:30.570 --> 01:44:34.170
and discourse growcommendable in none onlybut parrots.

2017
01:44:34.170 --> 01:44:35.830
Go in, sirrah.

2018
01:44:35.830 --> 01:44:37.030
Bid them prepare fordinner.

2019
01:44:37.030 --> 01:44:38.230
That is done, sir.

2020
01:44:38.230 --> 01:44:39.430
They have all stomachs.

2021
01:44:39.430 --> 01:44:43.100
Goodly lord, what awit-snapper are you.

2022
01:44:43.100 --> 01:44:46.270
Then bid them preparedinner.

2023
01:44:46.270 --> 01:44:47.370
Oh, that is done too, sir.

2024
01:44:47.370 --> 01:44:48.570
Only "cover" is the word.

2025
01:44:48.570 --> 01:44:49.770
Will you cover then, sir?

2026
01:44:49.770 --> 01:44:51.170
Not so, neither, sir.

2027
01:44:51.170 --> 01:44:52.270
I know my duty.

2028
01:44:52.270 --> 01:44:55.100
Yet more quarrelling withoccasion?

2029
01:44:55.100 --> 01:44:57.570
Wilt thou show the whole wealthof thy wit in an instant?

2030
01:44:57.570 --> 01:45:01.000
I pray thee understand a plainman in his plain meaning.

2031
01:45:01.000 --> 01:45:02.930
Go to thy fellows, bidthem cover the table,

2032
01:45:02.930 --> 01:45:06.170
serve in the meat, and wewill come in to dinner.

2033
01:45:06.170 --> 01:45:09.170
For the table, sir, itshall be served in.

